The paper discusses the development of a new concept of general-purpose intelligence cognition technology called Beyond AI, which aims to go beyond the limitations of current AI technology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also mentions the development of an intelligent learning model for automatic driving, precision medical care, and industrial robots, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG, cs.RO, and cs.SY sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of artificial life with an imagine function, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV sub-category.
